# Implementation Plan - Generate Safe Coping Guidance

Add a conversational/guidance path that turns current wellness context and stress analysis into practical, empathetic, and safe coping guidance (breathing, mindfulness, and motivational prompts). Guardrails will filter unsafe input and direct users to professional helplines.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Safety Guardrails**: If any input text (current journal entry text) matches crisis-related keywords (self-harm, suicide, doctor, diagnose, prescribe), we bypass typical coping tips and display a safe crisis support banner and disclaimer message directing the student to professional help (e.g., Vandrevala Foundation or AASRA helper lines).
>
> We will add the API endpoint `GET /v1/coping?user_id=<user_id>` that retrieves the latest journal entry for the user, checks it for safety, and generates a personalized guidance card payload containing:
> - `motivational_prompt`
> - `breathing_exercise`
> - `mindfulness_activity`
> - `is_safe` (boolean flag to indicate if crisis response is triggered)

